content:
To edit category group visibility, follow these steps:

You need View Data Categories in Setup permission.

Go to the data category visibility settings page in Setup. 

Enter Roles, Users, Permission Sets, or Profiles in the Quick Find box and select the relevant one.

Open a data category group for edit. For roles, click Edit next to the category group you want to modify. For permission sets and profiles, click Data Category Visibility then Edit next to the data category group you want to assign.

Select a visibility setting:

* All Categories: Users can see all categories in the category group.
* None: Users cannot see any categories in the category group.
* Custom: Users see your custom selection of categories. Select categories by double-clicking or selecting and clicking Add.

Categories that are grayed out are not available for selection because their parent has already been selected. Categories include child and parent categories when selected.

Click Save.

Data Category Visibility Best Practices:

* Create category groups with default visibility set to None.
* Grant visibility to categories, including child and parent categories.
* Assign visibility to users through roles, permission sets, or profiles.
* Users without assigned visibility can only see uncategorized articles unless they have the "View all Data" permission.
* Change category group visibility settings for each portal role on the Default Data Category Visibility page in Setup.
title: Editing Data Category Visibility in Salesforce Service Cloud
